'''TUGE Energia''' is a [[wind turbine manufacturer]] headquartered in [[Estonia]]. It manufactures and supplies [[small wind turbine]]s with capacity of 2, 10 and 50&nbsp;kW. 

The company was founded in 2015 in [[Tallinn]].<ref>Tuul, Harry. [http://www.aripaev.ee/uudised/2015/01/30/eesti-tuulikutoostus-tostab-pead "Eesti tuulikutööstus tõstab pead"], ''Äripäev'', Tallinn, 30 January 2015. Retrieved on 4 March 2016.</ref> At the beginning of 2017, it has more than 20 small wind turbines installed in [[Estonia]] and [[Finland]].<ref>[http://tuge.ee/en/references]. Retrieved on 4 March 2016.</ref> Company also provides complementary solar and battery storage solutions.

The company is a member of a [[World Wind Energy Association]].<ref>[http://small-wind.org/business-directory/1312/tuge-energia-ou/], ''WWEA Small Wind Platform''. Retrieved on 4 March 2016.</ref>

